WEBVTT

00:02.252 --> 00:04.880
♪♪

00:04.880 --> 00:06.882
[ Cellphone clicks ]

00:06.882 --> 00:09.468
I don't think new posters
are gonna cut it. What?

00:09.468 --> 00:12.888
You're gonna need to
up your campaign game.

00:12.888 --> 00:15.682
Well, perhaps my campaign
manager has some ideas.

00:15.682 --> 00:18.560
You mean besides
all the e‐mails I sent you?

00:18.560 --> 00:19.978
I should
probably read those.

00:19.978 --> 00:22.272
Nolan,
Lopez needs a unit

00:22.272 --> 00:23.815
to accompany her this morning,
and that's you.

00:23.815 --> 00:26.109
Yes, sir.
My pleasure. Uh, sir ‐‐

00:26.109 --> 00:28.237
Can I count on your vote?

00:28.237 --> 00:31.949
I'm still doing my due diligence
with the candidates.

00:31.949 --> 00:34.284
It's Smitty! You got my vote.

00:34.284 --> 00:35.827
Thank you.
Not mine.

00:35.827 --> 00:38.956
I'm not in
the union yet. Right.

00:38.956 --> 00:42.626
♪♪

00:42.626 --> 00:48.507
Looks like we're gonna be
riding together.

00:48.507 --> 00:50.175
Everything good?
Uh, yeah.

00:50.175 --> 00:52.427
We have to interview one of
these Sovereign Citizen idiots.

00:52.427 --> 00:54.388
He allegedly assaulted
an IRS agent

00:54.388 --> 00:56.932
who had a few questions
about why Marvin Reynolds

00:56.932 --> 00:58.433
wasn't paying
any of his taxes.

00:58.433 --> 01:00.143
Angela, I thought we were gonna
talk more this morning.

01:00.143 --> 01:01.103
I woke up,
you were gone.

01:01.103 --> 01:03.689
Yeah, I have a job,
remember? Uh...

01:03.689 --> 01:04.815
I'll wait for you
by the shop.

01:04.815 --> 01:08.819
I'm right behind you. Angela.

01:08.819 --> 01:10.654
I don't have time
for this conversation right now.

01:10.654 --> 01:12.906
How many times
can I apologize?

01:12.906 --> 01:15.993
[ Sighs ] I told you,
I didn't have a choice.

01:15.993 --> 01:17.744
Look, making a deal
with Elijah

01:17.744 --> 01:19.663
was the only way that I could
get you home safe.

01:19.663 --> 01:21.707
I understand why you did
what you did.

01:21.707 --> 01:23.709
I can even understand
why you kept it from me ‐‐

01:23.709 --> 01:25.294
you don't want to stress out
the new mom.

01:25.294 --> 01:27.337
But to tell me
I need to stay out of it

01:27.337 --> 01:28.630
after asking
for my help ‐‐

01:28.630 --> 01:31.466
Look, I didn't
mean for you ‐‐

01:31.466 --> 01:33.510
I got myself into this.

01:33.510 --> 01:35.137
No, you got <i>us</i>
into this,

01:35.137 --> 01:36.513
and I'm going to
get <i>us</i> out.

01:36.513 --> 01:37.931
Well, how do you plan
to do that?

01:37.931 --> 01:39.933
By telling Elijah Stone you
don't work for him anymore.

01:39.933 --> 01:41.143
And if he's got
a problem with that,

01:41.143 --> 01:42.811
me and a couple hundred
of my closest friends ‐‐

01:42.811 --> 01:46.356
No, you can't.
He has leverage on me.

01:46.356 --> 01:48.817
He could take it
to the state bar.

01:48.817 --> 01:50.068
I could lose
my license.

01:50.068 --> 01:52.696
Last night, you swore
you didn't break any laws.

01:52.696 --> 01:54.906
I haven't.

01:54.906 --> 01:58.577
There could be
some ethical questions.

01:58.577 --> 02:02.372
I can't do this
right now. We'll talk tonight.

02:02.372 --> 02:03.623
[ Sighs ]

02:03.623 --> 02:06.918
He can't really believe

02:06.918 --> 02:08.670
he can buy votes
with water bottles.

02:08.670 --> 02:10.422
I mean, not when I have
a real message,

02:10.422 --> 02:11.548
a message of change.

02:11.548 --> 02:13.175
Actually,
he's beating you.

02:13.175 --> 02:14.384
I did some polling,

02:14.384 --> 02:16.303
and you are
definitely behind.

02:16.303 --> 02:17.804
I'm losing to Smitty?

02:17.804 --> 02:19.181
Oh,
that's embarrassing.

02:19.181 --> 02:20.641
You know what would
really help?

02:20.641 --> 02:24.102
An endorsement from someone
respected within the department.

02:24.102 --> 02:26.521
No, don't drag me
into this.

02:26.521 --> 02:29.107
No, I have never endorsed
a candidate, and I never will.

02:29.107 --> 02:30.359
Voting is a private matter.

02:30.359 --> 02:31.652
[ Camera beeps ]

02:31.652 --> 02:34.780
Here, maybe this will help
wash away the taste of defeat.

02:34.780 --> 02:36.073
This bottle's
been opened.

02:36.073 --> 02:38.158
Oh, those bottles
are recyclable.

02:38.158 --> 02:40.118
It's just my way of giving back
to the environment.

02:40.118 --> 02:44.915
Where's the water from?
My bathroom sink. Water's water.

02:44.915 --> 02:48.043
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,
whoa, oh, oh ♪

02:48.043 --> 02:50.504
♪ I'm gonna win for you ♪

02:50.504 --> 02:54.383
♪ Like I know
you want me to do, hey ♪

02:54.383 --> 02:55.759
[ Cameras beep ]

02:55.759 --> 02:58.720
Everything okay
with you and Wesley? No.

02:58.720 --> 02:59.888
I get it.

02:59.888 --> 03:02.015
Sarah wanted to divorce me
at least three times

03:02.015 --> 03:03.725
during Henry's
first year.

03:03.725 --> 03:05.644
It felt like I couldn't
get anything right.

03:05.644 --> 03:07.062
It's rough,
those early days.

03:07.062 --> 03:10.065
You know, it's a lack of sleep,
it's fear of the unknown,

03:10.065 --> 03:11.525
a baby that
won't stop crying ‐‐‐

03:11.525 --> 03:15.404
It's not about that.
What is it about?

03:15.404 --> 03:17.614
Right now, it's about you
not minding your own business.

03:17.614 --> 03:19.783
Put the shop in drive
and let's go.

03:19.783 --> 03:20.992
I will have to
put it in reverse

03:20.992 --> 03:22.786
before I can
actually put it ‐‐

03:22.786 --> 03:24.746
I know that look.
No more jokes.

03:24.746 --> 03:26.957
[ Engine starts ]

03:26.957 --> 03:33.880
Tim: Genny. Sergeant Bradford.

03:33.880 --> 03:38.135
You look skinny.
Have you been eating?

03:38.135 --> 03:39.761
Every day.
Uh‐huh.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.555
This is a restricted area.
How'd you get in here?

03:41.555 --> 03:43.723
Oh, the guy who's
handing out waters let me in.

03:43.723 --> 03:48.019
Okay. Yeah.
Don't drink that. Um...

03:48.019 --> 03:49.104
So, what are you
doing here?

03:49.104 --> 03:51.440
I just wanted to
see my big brother.

03:51.440 --> 03:53.984
Oh, hi.
I'm Lucy Chen.

03:53.984 --> 03:55.026
I know that
we just met,

03:55.026 --> 03:56.361
but if you have
any embarrassing stories

03:56.361 --> 03:58.238
from his childhood,
that ‐‐

03:58.238 --> 03:59.865
[ Bottle crinkles ]

03:59.865 --> 04:02.659
So you just
wanted to see me?

04:02.659 --> 04:04.494
I didn't even know
you were in town.

04:04.494 --> 04:05.954
So you're not just not
returning my calls,

04:05.954 --> 04:06.955
you're also ignoring
the messages

04:06.955 --> 04:08.206
telling you
I'm coming to town.

04:08.206 --> 04:09.416
Because I know
why you're here,

04:09.416 --> 04:13.003
and I've made
my position very clear.

04:13.003 --> 04:15.422
We have to
talk about it.

04:15.422 --> 04:16.506
Look, I gotta
get to work.

04:16.506 --> 04:18.467
Maybe we can
have dinner tonight.

04:18.467 --> 04:20.635
[ Scoffs ] So you can
blow me off at the last minute?

04:20.635 --> 04:22.763
No.

04:22.763 --> 04:25.974
Why don't I do one of those
ride‐along thingies?

04:25.974 --> 04:29.227
That way, we could have
the whole day to catch up. Yeah.

04:29.227 --> 04:32.147
See, you gotta get permission
to do a ride‐along. It's ‐‐

04:32.147 --> 04:33.565
It's a long process,
a ton of paperwork.

04:33.565 --> 04:34.566
Hey, you're
a sergeant now.

04:34.566 --> 04:37.569
You can just
approve it yourself. Great.

04:37.569 --> 04:44.367
Let's hit the streets. Let's.
Did Tim have any, um,

04:44.367 --> 04:46.536
nicknames
when he was a kid?

04:46.536 --> 04:52.834
♪♪

04:52.834 --> 04:55.253
So, it's been
six weeks.

04:55.253 --> 04:57.464
Any thoughts
on my progress?

04:57.464 --> 04:59.341
I write an evaluation
every day.

04:59.341 --> 05:02.135
Those are my thoughts
on your progress.

05:02.135 --> 05:03.845
Right, I mean,
that's the technical stuff,

05:03.845 --> 05:05.388
but I was just
wondering, like,

05:05.388 --> 05:08.725
what you thought of me
as a person.

05:08.725 --> 05:10.852
What matters is what
I think about you as a cop.

05:10.852 --> 05:14.439
You want people to like you,
go make some friends.

05:14.439 --> 05:16.983
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

05:16.983 --> 05:24.407
Harper. What?

05:24.407 --> 05:25.534
Oh, no, no.

05:25.534 --> 05:26.993
This is the first
I'm hearing about this.

05:26.993 --> 05:27.994
[ Stammers ]

05:27.994 --> 05:32.332
He can't do that,
though, right?

05:32.332 --> 05:33.917
Maybe?
W‐What do you mean maybe?

05:33.917 --> 05:35.043
You ‐‐
You are the lawyer.

05:35.043 --> 05:37.337
Shouldn't you know that
for sure?

05:37.337 --> 05:38.755
Okay, well,
I‐I'ma need you

05:38.755 --> 05:43.301
to get some damn clarity
and call me back.

05:43.301 --> 05:45.762
Is everything okay?
No.

05:45.762 --> 05:47.138
[ Scoffs ]

05:47.138 --> 05:49.558
My ex‐husband
is getting married,

05:49.558 --> 05:51.393
and he wants to move
to San Francisco

05:51.393 --> 05:55.480
and take my daughter
with him. Can he do that?

05:55.480 --> 05:57.357
I don't know.

05:57.357 --> 06:00.986
This is Detective Angela Lopez,
badge number 1777.

06:00.986 --> 06:03.947
I need complete histories,
statewide and CJIC,

06:03.947 --> 06:05.532
for the personal
file numbers ‐‐

06:05.532 --> 06:10.954
NWC‐057, JPA‐733,
BXR‐389.

06:10.954 --> 06:13.373
And if any of those queries
generate other file numbers,

06:13.373 --> 06:16.251
can I get completes
on those, too? Thanks.

06:16.251 --> 06:17.752
[ Cellphone clicks ]

06:17.752 --> 06:18.962
What was that about?

06:18.962 --> 06:21.047
Uh, another case
I'm working on.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.591
Anything
I can help with?

06:22.591 --> 06:24.593
No, I got it handled.

06:24.593 --> 06:27.345
Genny:
Oh, yeah, he tried to highlight
his hair right before prom.

06:27.345 --> 06:29.222
He ended up
looking like Slim Shady.

06:29.222 --> 06:30.515
Hm!
Oh, you know what?

06:30.515 --> 06:31.766
I think I have a picture of it.

06:31.766 --> 06:34.269
Oh, my God, yes!
Genny.

06:34.269 --> 06:36.438
What, you'd ‐‐ you'd rather
I keep this photo private?

06:36.438 --> 06:39.816
That's fine.
Let's talk about dad.

06:39.816 --> 06:43.028
I have nothing to say. Okay.

06:43.028 --> 06:44.487
What's your cellphone number?
I'll text it to you.

06:44.487 --> 06:46.990
Genny, come on. We don't
need your distractions.

06:46.990 --> 06:48.533
Police work
is serious stuff.

06:48.533 --> 06:49.910
[ Horn honks ]

06:49.910 --> 06:52.078
[ Bicycle bell rings ]

06:52.078 --> 06:54.039
Ooh, boy.

06:54.039 --> 06:55.832
[ Bell ringing ]

06:55.832 --> 06:58.126
♪♪

06:58.126 --> 06:59.878
[ Brakes squeak ]

06:59.878 --> 07:01.463
[ Gear shift clicks ]

07:01.463 --> 07:04.674
♪♪

07:04.674 --> 07:06.343
♪♪

07:06.343 --> 07:08.887
Tim: Hey, ma'am, I'm gonna
need you to pull over.

07:08.887 --> 07:10.930
[ Slurring ]
You'll never catch me!

07:10.930 --> 07:12.641
Have you been
drinking?

07:12.641 --> 07:15.977
It's not illegal
to drink and bike.

07:15.977 --> 07:17.145
Actually, it is.

07:17.145 --> 07:19.189
The way you were swerving
in and out of traffic ‐‐

07:19.189 --> 07:21.024
Oh. Uh...

07:21.024 --> 07:22.901
You could have caused
an accident. Alright?

07:22.901 --> 07:28.323
I just wanna get some tacos!
Don't be such a butt.

07:28.323 --> 07:30.617
Okay, ma'am, we can cite you
for public intoxication,

07:30.617 --> 07:33.536
or if you don't cooperate,
we'll charge you with a DUI.

07:33.536 --> 07:38.958
Screw you, you
Ken‐doll‐ass‐looking mimbo ‐‐

07:38.958 --> 07:40.001
Hey, honey.

07:40.001 --> 07:41.169
Honey, I know
you're having a bad day,

07:41.169 --> 07:42.671
but that doesn't give you
the right to be rude.

07:42.671 --> 07:44.714
They're just doing
their jobs.

07:44.714 --> 07:46.341
Why don't you take
a few deep breaths

07:46.341 --> 07:52.430
and sit down
for a minute? I'm sorry.

07:52.430 --> 07:55.100
♪♪

07:55.100 --> 07:56.851
That was impressive.

07:56.851 --> 07:58.353
I teach
fourth graders.

07:58.353 --> 08:02.607
♪♪

08:02.607 --> 08:04.025
Oh, great.

08:04.025 --> 08:07.070
Okay, look, you cannot move
our daughter to San Francisco.

08:07.070 --> 08:08.446
What ‐‐ What ‐‐
What are we gonna do?

08:08.446 --> 08:10.573
Put her on a plane
every weekend?

08:10.573 --> 08:11.574
Enroll her
in two schools?

08:11.574 --> 08:13.034
No, obviously not.

08:13.034 --> 08:15.370
What you are asking for
is near total custody

08:15.370 --> 08:17.622
and I see her on weekends
and holidays, which ‐‐

08:17.622 --> 08:21.042
which is a violation of our
custody agreement, by the way,

08:21.042 --> 08:23.294
so I ‐‐
I'm gonna need ‐‐
[ Cellphone beeps ]

08:23.294 --> 08:25.380
Voicemail:
<i>If you're satisfied with</i>
<i>your message, press one.</i>

08:25.380 --> 08:27.048
<i>If you'd like to</i>
<i>re‐record, pre‐‐</i>

08:27.048 --> 08:29.008
[ Cellphone clicks ]

08:29.008 --> 08:31.219
Look, I know he's
your daughter's father,

08:31.219 --> 08:35.849
but that man is a coward
for springing this on you.

08:35.849 --> 08:39.853
Well, he might have
left a message last week

08:39.853 --> 08:42.689
saying that he needed to talk
to me about something, but ‐‐

08:42.689 --> 08:45.066
Maybe it was two messages.

08:45.066 --> 08:48.236
There might have been
an e‐mail. But...

08:48.236 --> 08:49.779
Okay. Then, why didn't you
call him back?

08:49.779 --> 08:51.906
I don't know. I thought
it was about something else.

08:51.906 --> 08:55.368
Oh, so you were
avoiding him? No, I was n‐‐

08:55.368 --> 08:57.287
I don't know. Maybe.

08:57.287 --> 09:02.959
I did‐‐ I didn't want to
have to talk about... Halloween.

09:02.959 --> 09:06.296
What happened
on Halloween?

09:06.296 --> 09:10.258
Ohhh.
Mm. Lopez: Sorry.

09:10.258 --> 09:12.385
Well, we're about to land
at Marvin Reynolds' place.

09:12.385 --> 09:13.553
What are we
hoping for?

09:13.553 --> 09:15.555
Ideally, he admits to
assaulting the IRS agent

09:15.555 --> 09:16.556
and we hook him up.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.058
Otherwise, it's just
a misdemeanor

09:18.058 --> 09:20.518
not committed
in police presence.

09:20.518 --> 09:23.104
His word against
the IRS agent's.

09:23.104 --> 09:24.981
Yeah, I always mix up these
Sovereign Citizen guys

09:24.981 --> 09:27.901
with the
Posse Comitatus group.

09:27.901 --> 09:28.985
They're all just part of

09:28.985 --> 09:31.696
the same crazy,
anti‐government soup ‐‐

09:31.696 --> 09:34.657
all just looking for their way
not to pay their fair share.

09:34.657 --> 09:36.451
I think there's a little
more to it than that.

09:36.451 --> 09:38.203
Good for you.

09:38.203 --> 09:39.788
Look, there's always
people in society

09:39.788 --> 09:41.915
who feel like
they're on the outside.

09:41.915 --> 09:44.292
And some are
easily manipulated.

09:44.292 --> 09:46.628
Some are so desperate
to find a purpose

09:46.628 --> 09:48.588
that they allow themselves
to be infected

09:48.588 --> 09:50.131
by the most absurd
beliefs,

09:50.131 --> 09:52.050
so much so,
they could rationalize

09:52.050 --> 09:55.136
beating up
an IRS agent ‐‐ or worse.

09:55.136 --> 09:57.097
Nah.
My theory's better.

09:57.097 --> 09:59.599
These whack jobs just believe
they're above the law,

09:59.599 --> 10:04.145
until they need it. There it is.

10:04.145 --> 10:05.313
[ Sighs ]

10:05.313 --> 10:07.440
[ Dog barking in distance ]

10:07.440 --> 10:09.359
[ Gearshift clicks ]

10:14.072 --> 10:15.907
[ Vehicle door closes ]

10:15.907 --> 10:17.867
This guy have
a history of violence?

10:17.867 --> 10:20.078
Why do you think
I'm putting on a vest?

10:20.078 --> 10:23.039
Let me guess.
Domestic abuse?

10:23.039 --> 10:25.208
Among other things,
but he never did any time.

10:32.841 --> 10:34.676
Hey, get the hell off
of my property!

10:34.676 --> 10:37.512
Sir, I'm Detective Lopez,
and this is Officer Nolan.

10:37.512 --> 10:38.721
Are you
Marvin Reynolds?

10:38.721 --> 10:40.598
You know what?
That name is a straw‐man, okay?

10:40.598 --> 10:42.725
I'm a free man,
I'm living upon the land.

10:42.725 --> 10:44.602
You're representatives of
a corporate government.

10:44.602 --> 10:46.312
You have no authority
over me.

10:46.312 --> 10:49.232
I am not a citizen of
your corporation!

10:49.232 --> 10:51.151
Sir, a complaint's been
filed against you

10:51.151 --> 10:53.653
claiming you assaulted
a federal employee from the IRS.

10:53.653 --> 10:56.197
Yeah, they're trying to
take my house. Okay?

10:56.197 --> 10:57.991
But, see, there's no
legitimate money,

10:57.991 --> 11:00.535
because we went off
the gold standard in 1933.

11:00.535 --> 11:03.788
So you're admitting
to the assault?

11:03.788 --> 11:05.456
No, I admit nothing, okay?

11:05.456 --> 11:07.333
And I don't ‐‐ I don't ‐‐
I don't have any obligation

11:07.333 --> 11:09.252
to submit
to your unlawful inquiry.

11:09.252 --> 11:10.962
Sir, we need to talk to you
about what happened.

11:10.962 --> 11:12.630
Can you please step out
onto the porch?

11:12.630 --> 11:16.885
I'm a constitutional activist,
okay? I know my rights.

11:16.885 --> 11:19.679
A‐A‐And what you're
practicing here, it's tyranny.

11:19.679 --> 11:22.015
Sir, we just want
your side of the story.

11:22.015 --> 11:24.225
I promise you, this will be
much more productive

11:24.225 --> 11:27.395
if you just step out
onto the porch. Ah. [ Chuckles ]

11:27.395 --> 11:31.441
Yeah, that's ‐‐
that's not gonna happen. Okay?

11:31.441 --> 11:39.032
So get off of my property.
Now. Sir, take it easy.

11:39.032 --> 11:40.742
Don't do anything stupid.

11:40.742 --> 11:43.286
♪♪

11:43.286 --> 11:44.996
Sir?

11:44.996 --> 11:46.623
Lopez: Gun!
Move, move, move!

11:46.623 --> 11:48.666
[ Automatic gunfire ]

11:48.666 --> 11:49.876
[ Glass shattering ]

11:49.876 --> 11:51.419
[ Radio chirps ]
7‐Adam‐15.

11:51.419 --> 11:54.339
Shots fired at our location.
Send backup, Code 3.

11:54.339 --> 11:56.716
You ready?
Yeah.

11:56.716 --> 11:58.092
[ Door bangs in distance ]

11:58.092 --> 11:59.677
He's going outside.
He's running.

11:59.677 --> 12:01.137
[ Dog barking in distance ]

12:01.137 --> 12:06.601
♪♪

12:06.601 --> 12:12.065
♪♪

12:12.065 --> 12:14.901
[ Dog growling ]

12:14.901 --> 12:18.196
♪♪

12:18.196 --> 12:20.240
[ Engine starts ]
No!

12:20.240 --> 12:21.866
[ Tires squeal ]

12:21.866 --> 12:26.537
Control, 7‐Adam‐15.
Code 3 traffic.

12:26.537 --> 12:28.873
We just got 246'd
by a submachine gun.

12:28.873 --> 12:30.959
Suspect vehicle ‐‐
silver sedan,

12:30.959 --> 12:34.499
last seen headed west
on Oakwood. Suspect still armed.

12:38.268 --> 12:40.020
Air Three
is lifting now.

12:40.020 --> 12:42.189
I'm ten‐nine‐seven.
Searching for suspect's vehicle.

12:42.189 --> 12:44.149
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

12:44.149 --> 12:46.693
Control, 7‐Adam‐100
on scene.

12:46.693 --> 12:48.904
[ Sirens wail ]

12:48.904 --> 12:50.030
[ Tires screech ]

12:50.030 --> 12:53.325
Stay in the car. Anybody hurt?

12:53.325 --> 12:55.244
We're good, but we've got
one shooter outstanding ‐‐

12:55.244 --> 12:56.578
Marvin Reynolds.

12:56.578 --> 12:58.121
Suspect vehicle ‐‐
silver sedan.

12:58.121 --> 13:00.040
Did not get very good I. D.
I didn't get any plates.

13:00.040 --> 13:01.208
Alright, let's pull
DMV records,

13:01.208 --> 13:02.584
see what Marvin's
got registered.

13:02.584 --> 13:04.586
Got to find everything
we can about this guy.
On it.

13:04.586 --> 13:05.754
I'll ask for
a telephonic warrant

13:05.754 --> 13:07.589
to search the GPS of
his vehicle on his phone.

13:07.589 --> 13:08.632
If we can see where he's been,

13:08.632 --> 13:09.967
it might help us know
where he's going.

13:09.967 --> 13:11.635
Control, 7‐Adam‐100,
advise crime scene

13:11.635 --> 13:13.345
they can begin processing
and start a board‐up crew.

13:13.345 --> 13:16.014
And I need all available units
for a city‐wide manhunt.

13:16.014 --> 13:18.809
Tim: Alright, listen up ‐‐
at approximately 1057 hours,

13:18.809 --> 13:20.352
suspect Marvin Reynolds
opened fire

13:20.352 --> 13:21.812
on Officer Nolan
and Detective Lopez

13:21.812 --> 13:22.896
with a submachine gun.

13:22.896 --> 13:24.231
We're dealing with
a Sovereign Citizen

13:24.231 --> 13:25.399
who's clearly snapped.

13:25.399 --> 13:27.776
He assaulted an IRS agent
who showed up two days ago

13:27.776 --> 13:29.278
to start foreclosure
proceedings.

13:29.278 --> 13:30.988
We're gonna hit up
every known address,

13:30.988 --> 13:33.073
every relative's address,
every associate,

13:33.073 --> 13:34.867
every friend of a friend
of a friend

13:34.867 --> 13:36.410
until someone
coughs this guy up.

13:36.410 --> 13:38.912
Okay, he hasn't renewed
any of his registrations
in over four years,

13:38.912 --> 13:41.290
but I got a list of everything
he's owned going back to 2005.

13:41.290 --> 13:43.000
You got a silver Honda
on there or a Toyota?

13:43.000 --> 13:44.918
There's a silver Civic,
as well as three other vehicles.

13:44.918 --> 13:46.169
Alright, send that list
to everyone's boxes.

13:46.169 --> 13:47.170
Make sure
you keep checking.

13:47.170 --> 13:49.131
This is a very fluid
situation.

13:49.131 --> 13:51.049
Now let's go get this guy
before he does something worse.

13:51.049 --> 13:54.303
Phew. What's going on?

13:54.303 --> 13:55.679
I'm taking you
back to the station.
It's too dangerous.

13:55.679 --> 13:57.055
[ Scoffs ] Forget it.
Genny.

13:57.055 --> 13:59.224
I'm not leaving until
we talk about dad.

13:59.224 --> 14:02.269
Oh, you are impossible.
<i>I'm</i> impossible?

14:02.269 --> 14:03.937
Lucy, who's more difficult,
me or Tim?

14:03.937 --> 14:05.647
Of course
she's gonna pick me!

14:05.647 --> 14:07.232
Because you are the most
stubborn person alive,

14:07.232 --> 14:08.692
which is, by the way,
why you're still single.

14:08.692 --> 14:10.694
[ Scoffs ] Okay.
First of all, I'm not.

14:10.694 --> 14:11.987
And second ‐‐
Wait. What?

14:11.987 --> 14:13.947
You're seeing someone?
This is insane.

14:13.947 --> 14:18.118
There is an armed and dangerous
suspect at large. We gotta focus.

14:18.118 --> 14:19.870
[ Engine starts,
gearshift clicks ]

14:23.415 --> 14:25.083
[ Keyboard clicking ]

14:25.083 --> 14:26.418
Are you okay?

14:26.418 --> 14:28.211
I'm fine.
I've been shot at before.

14:28.211 --> 14:29.713
That's not what
I'm talking about.

14:29.713 --> 14:31.298
Something else
is going on here,

14:31.298 --> 14:36.511
and maybe a friendly ear
will help.

14:36.511 --> 14:38.388
Wesley made a deal
with Elijah Stone

14:38.388 --> 14:41.016
to find out where La Fiera
was keeping me in Guatemala,

14:41.016 --> 14:46.480
and now Elijah is
threatening our family.

14:46.480 --> 14:48.940
What do we do?

14:48.940 --> 14:50.984
Thank you, but I'm trying to
figure that out.

14:50.984 --> 14:52.486
Well, it doesn't seem
that complicated.

14:52.486 --> 14:55.113
He's a criminal,
and you're a cop.

14:55.113 --> 14:58.367
There's an element I can't talk
about, but it muddies things.

14:58.367 --> 15:02.162
Well, for what it's worth,

15:02.162 --> 15:05.040
I have never met a couple
so different from each other

15:05.040 --> 15:07.292
and yet so perfect
for one another.

15:07.292 --> 15:09.461
I can't imagine what it is
you're facing,

15:09.461 --> 15:11.046
but I do know this ‐‐

15:11.046 --> 15:18.053
the only way you're gonna
get through it is together.

15:18.053 --> 15:20.681
Pull over. You gonna throw up?

15:20.681 --> 15:21.807
Was that a little
too saccharine?

15:21.807 --> 15:23.558
A little,
but I need to make a call.

15:23.558 --> 15:25.852
I've been known to
keep a secret.

15:25.852 --> 15:26.978
I need to make a call,

15:26.978 --> 15:28.480
and unless you want to
be subpoenaed one day,

15:28.480 --> 15:32.275
you can't hear any of it,
so pull over. Roger that.

15:41.910 --> 15:44.287
[ Video chat ringing ]

15:44.287 --> 15:46.289
Hey, it's me.

15:46.289 --> 15:47.374
Hey.
Are we okay?

15:47.374 --> 15:49.626
<i>I'm working on it.</i>
I've been digging

15:49.626 --> 15:51.461
into everything I can find
about Elijah,

15:51.461 --> 15:52.879
and I think I have a plan.

15:52.879 --> 15:54.965
We're going to build
a RICO case against him

15:54.965 --> 15:57.092
and make sure
he rots in jail,

15:57.092 --> 15:59.720
which means I need you to
document every interaction

15:59.720 --> 16:00.971
you've ever had
with Elijah ‐‐

16:00.971 --> 16:02.973
every threat
or implied threat,

16:02.973 --> 16:04.516
admission
to his own crimes

16:04.516 --> 16:06.226
or the crimes of
his criminal enterprise.

16:06.226 --> 16:07.602
No, I can't.

16:07.602 --> 16:09.479
That violates
attorney‐client privilege.

16:09.479 --> 16:11.314
Are you serious?
I know.

16:11.314 --> 16:13.400
He threatened
your wife and baby.

16:13.400 --> 16:15.277
The privilege belongs
to the client.

16:15.277 --> 16:18.363
It's not my privilege
to waive. You made a vow.

16:18.363 --> 16:19.364
What's more important,

16:19.364 --> 16:21.450
your vow to your client
or to me?

16:21.450 --> 16:22.743
[ Sighs ]

16:22.743 --> 16:26.538
Oh, up on the right ‐‐
silver one.

16:26.538 --> 16:29.708
No, wrong make
and model.

16:29.708 --> 16:31.960
Any other plans
while you're in L. A.?

16:31.960 --> 16:34.463
I have to sell our dad's house.

16:34.463 --> 16:36.214
He hasn't been able to live
on his own for awhile.

16:36.214 --> 16:40.469
Oh. I'm sorry.
Thanks. It's a mess.

16:40.469 --> 16:41.887
It's a lot of work
for one person.

16:41.887 --> 16:43.305
Well, I'm sure
Tim will help.

16:43.305 --> 16:44.806
What's the point?
It's a teardown.

16:44.806 --> 16:46.808
Just sell it
and be done with it.

16:46.808 --> 16:48.101
It's got good bones.

16:48.101 --> 16:49.811
We could make some money
if we put in a little effort.

16:49.811 --> 16:52.439
You watch a couple hours of HGTV
and now you're an expert?

16:52.439 --> 16:54.107
Wait, what is
your favorite show?

16:54.107 --> 16:55.734
Mine is "House Hunters
International."

16:55.734 --> 16:57.444
Oh, my God. The best.

16:57.444 --> 16:59.279
Nolan, can you 10‐3
to another channel?

16:59.279 --> 17:01.364
Roger that.
Going to 6.

17:01.364 --> 17:03.658
Yeah, look, my sister needs
to sell my dad's house,

17:03.658 --> 17:04.951
<i>but it hasn't been</i>
<i>updated or repaired</i>

17:04.951 --> 17:06.495
<i>since it was built</i>
<i>in 1958.</i>

17:06.495 --> 17:10.123
What are the inspections
gonna reveal? Uh, 1958?

17:10.123 --> 17:12.334
It's probably got old
cloth‐insulated wiring

17:12.334 --> 17:13.919
that would need to
be replaced.

17:13.919 --> 17:15.962
Uh, the plumbing would
need to be updated.

17:15.962 --> 17:17.964
<i>The cast‐iron sewer</i>
<i>could be cracked</i>

17:17.964 --> 17:19.174
or rusted through
in places,

17:19.174 --> 17:21.009
and the foundations
would need to be checked.

17:21.009 --> 17:22.344
So it's a teardown.

17:22.344 --> 17:23.637
<i>Oh, no,</i>
<i>not necessarily.</i>

17:23.637 --> 17:24.638
If it has good bones,

17:24.638 --> 17:26.097
some simple repairs
and updates

17:26.097 --> 17:28.391
<i>would double the value</i>
<i>of your house.</i>

17:28.391 --> 17:29.643
I'm happy to swing by,
take a look at it,

17:29.643 --> 17:30.727
see what needs
to be done.

17:30.727 --> 17:32.813
Alright, you will all
have to wait your turn.

17:32.813 --> 17:37.150
Nolan is busy helping me install
my new kitchen backsplash.

17:37.150 --> 17:38.568
Right, but after that.

17:38.568 --> 17:40.112
Kind of regretting
telling everyone

17:40.112 --> 17:41.613
you used to be a contractor,
aren't you?

17:41.613 --> 17:43.365
Aaron: <i>Hey, Nolan,</i>
<i>do you do pergolas?</i>

17:43.365 --> 17:45.700
'Cause my outdoor space
is really underused.

17:45.700 --> 17:47.911
Landscaping's not really
my area of expertise,

17:47.911 --> 17:49.871
but I have built
a gazebo or two in my day.

17:49.871 --> 17:51.706
Hold on. We just
got sent a location

17:51.706 --> 17:54.084
of one of Marvin Reynolds'
vehicles.

17:54.084 --> 17:55.794
Looks like he's got an RV

17:55.794 --> 17:57.212
that's been collecting
parking tickets

17:57.212 --> 17:59.297
on the 1600 block
of Crenshaw.

17:59.297 --> 18:00.799
We're closest.
We'll ‐‐ We'll take it.

18:00.799 --> 18:02.551
[ Engine revs ]
Heading there now.

18:04.636 --> 18:06.680
[ Cellphone chimes ]

18:06.680 --> 18:11.685
Is that from
your lawyer? Uh, yeah.

18:11.685 --> 18:13.562
It's about
three pages of legalese

18:13.562 --> 18:16.189
that basically comes down to,
I am screwed.

18:16.189 --> 18:17.190
Yeah, but
you're the mom.

18:17.190 --> 18:18.859
I mean,
that has to matter.

18:18.859 --> 18:20.861
Yeah, I'm the mom who all
but abandoned her daughter

18:20.861 --> 18:23.363
when I went undercover
and then nearly got her killed.

18:23.363 --> 18:25.240
Donovan is the one
who was there for her.

18:25.240 --> 18:26.658
Okay, but that
was the past.

18:26.658 --> 18:30.412
Look, I've seen you,
okay? You're a great mom.

18:30.412 --> 18:33.123
Would a great mom put her kid
through a second custody battle?

18:33.123 --> 18:34.916
I mean, last time
was a nightmare.

18:34.916 --> 18:37.711
She had trouble sleeping.
Her school work suffered.

18:37.711 --> 18:40.255
I just ‐‐ I don't know
if I can do that again.

18:40.255 --> 18:41.840
There's our RV.
Alright.

18:41.840 --> 18:47.762
Be ready to bail in case
he opens fire on us. Got that.

18:47.762 --> 18:49.472
[ Engine turns off ]

18:49.472 --> 18:53.143
♪♪

18:53.143 --> 18:58.273
♪♪

18:58.273 --> 19:03.445
♪♪

19:03.445 --> 19:05.238
♪♪

19:05.238 --> 19:09.826
♪♪

19:09.826 --> 19:13.079
Yeah, VIN matches.
This is our guy's.

19:13.079 --> 19:18.627
Looks abandoned, but it don't
mean he ain't held up inside.

19:18.627 --> 19:20.212
Alright.
What's the play, Boot?

19:20.212 --> 19:22.005
Well, there's only
one entry point,

19:22.005 --> 19:24.549
so we stay safe
and, uh, try to see

19:24.549 --> 19:26.134
if we can get him to come out
with verbal commands.

19:26.134 --> 19:31.223
And if there's
no response? Breach? Or...

19:31.223 --> 19:35.060
♪♪

19:35.060 --> 19:40.106
♪♪

19:40.106 --> 19:41.358
Harper: Ball‐Cam.

19:41.358 --> 19:44.069
360‐degree view.
It can even swim.

19:44.069 --> 19:47.072
I am in no mood to play games
with this guy.

19:47.072 --> 19:51.201
We just have to
get it inside.

19:51.201 --> 19:55.288
♪♪

19:55.288 --> 19:59.668
♪♪

19:59.668 --> 20:01.336
[ Glass shatters ]

20:01.336 --> 20:03.463
♪♪

20:03.463 --> 20:08.510
♪♪

20:08.510 --> 20:10.011
[ Ball‐Cam whirs ]

20:10.011 --> 20:12.097
Man.

20:12.097 --> 20:14.349
This guy
is ready for war.

20:14.349 --> 20:16.434
So, are we going in?
Hold on. One sec.

20:16.434 --> 20:17.602
I gotta
check the door,

20:17.602 --> 20:19.729
make sure it's not rigged
with explosives.

20:19.729 --> 20:21.398
Yeah, he definitely
seems like the type.

20:21.398 --> 20:23.400
Alright,
I don't see any wires.

20:23.400 --> 20:25.235
We're all clear.

20:25.235 --> 20:28.822
♪♪

20:28.822 --> 20:30.782
[ Crowbar clangs ]

20:30.782 --> 20:36.037
♪♪

20:36.037 --> 20:40.834
♪♪

20:40.834 --> 20:42.627
Alright.
We're all clear.

20:42.627 --> 20:46.464
Control, 7‐Adam‐07,
we're code 4. RV is unoccupied.

20:46.464 --> 20:47.549
[ Radio chirps ]

20:47.549 --> 20:50.468
"Rebirth through
the blood of innocents."

20:50.468 --> 20:51.726
Looks like we got ourselves
a manifesto.

20:55.478 --> 20:57.647
Control, Air Three is moving
over to the northeast grid.

20:57.647 --> 20:58.981
Control: <i>Copy, Air Three.</i>

20:58.981 --> 21:00.608
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

21:00.608 --> 21:02.401
Listen to this ‐‐

21:02.401 --> 21:06.656
"Satanic‐Hebrew Anglo‐Commerce
devoured America."

21:06.656 --> 21:08.699
"The Cabal's slaves
have vanquished us.

21:08.699 --> 21:10.451
Your blood flows
gutter‐rivers today."

21:10.451 --> 21:12.537
"The time is at hand
for renewal,

21:12.537 --> 21:14.831
and we will use
the blood of the masters

21:14.831 --> 21:17.667
to wash away
the incestuous sins

21:17.667 --> 21:19.919
of the corrupt
adjudicators."

21:19.919 --> 21:22.547
Barely literate
and yet truly terrifying.

21:22.547 --> 21:24.966
The good news is, we found
the RV with his stash of guns

21:24.966 --> 21:26.300
before he could
get to them.

21:26.300 --> 21:27.760
Even if all he has
is a submachine gun,

21:27.760 --> 21:29.929
we're still looking at a
potential mass‐casualty event.

21:29.929 --> 21:31.889
Nolan: He post anything
to social media?

21:31.889 --> 21:35.059
Nothing new. A dozen older
posts, tilting at windmills.

21:35.059 --> 21:37.019
But he's only got
like 10 followers.

21:37.019 --> 21:38.938
Not sure how wide
his message spread.

21:38.938 --> 21:40.982
Maybe he's using a secret
platform, like 9‐Chan?

21:40.982 --> 21:42.233
Forensics is on that.

21:42.233 --> 21:44.610
[ Computer beeps ]

21:44.610 --> 21:46.028
Got a name
and work address

21:46.028 --> 21:47.864
of a former girlfriend ‐‐
Erica Lawrence.

21:47.864 --> 21:49.574
Multiple domestic calls
to her home

21:49.574 --> 21:50.741
when they were together.

21:50.741 --> 21:55.788
Grey wants us
to interview her. Right.

21:55.788 --> 22:00.418
I think that's her.
Yeah. [ Sighs ]

22:00.418 --> 22:05.131
That should be her.
Lopez: Ms. Lawrence? Erica: Yes?

22:05.131 --> 22:07.800
I'm Detective Lopez.
This is Officer Nolan.

22:07.800 --> 22:10.386
Can you tell us the last time
you saw Marvin Reynolds?

22:10.386 --> 22:12.305
What'd he do?

22:12.305 --> 22:15.266
Shot at us,
for starters. Have you seen him?

22:15.266 --> 22:18.102
Not since last month.

22:18.102 --> 22:21.272
I started dating someone,
and he found out.

22:21.272 --> 22:22.857
I was so careful
about posting anything,

22:22.857 --> 22:26.736
but somehow, he knew.
What happened?

22:26.736 --> 22:28.404
He came over drunk.

22:28.404 --> 22:31.449
He insisted on playing
Russian Roulette.

22:31.449 --> 22:34.452
He said that
if I deserved to live, that...

22:34.452 --> 22:36.329
fate would save me.

22:36.329 --> 22:37.955
H‐He pulled the trigger
three times

22:37.955 --> 22:42.001
before my brother came
and scared him off. I'm so sorry.

22:42.001 --> 22:44.754
And you didn't file
a restraining order?

22:44.754 --> 22:47.340
I was too scared.

22:47.340 --> 22:49.884
I just want him
to forget I exist.

22:49.884 --> 22:51.677
But now, do y‐‐

22:51.677 --> 22:54.305
do you think that
he would come for me?

22:54.305 --> 22:55.640
We won't let him.

22:55.640 --> 22:57.141
I'll have a unit come
take you to the station

22:57.141 --> 22:58.809
and wait
until we catch him.

22:58.809 --> 22:59.977
Is there anything
you can tell us

22:59.977 --> 23:03.272
that might help us do that? Um...

23:03.272 --> 23:06.108
He used to boast
that he had weapons

23:06.108 --> 23:08.778
stashed all over the city,
but he never said where.

23:08.778 --> 23:12.531
What was he gonna
use them for? Killing people.

23:12.531 --> 23:15.993
But I‐I don't know
who, exactly.

23:15.993 --> 23:17.411
He wasn't always like this.

23:17.411 --> 23:20.748
When I first met him,
he was intense and a bit quiet,

23:20.748 --> 23:23.751
but he wasn't radicalized.
Well, what changed?

23:23.751 --> 23:26.921
He met this guy online ‐‐
Cooper.

23:26.921 --> 23:29.966
He's the one who pulled him
into the Sovereign Citizens.

23:29.966 --> 23:32.343
Any idea where
we can find Cooper?

23:32.343 --> 23:34.345
You know, you'd think
after the seventh time

23:34.345 --> 23:36.389
this guy posted about
overthrowing the government,

23:36.389 --> 23:37.640
someone might have
called us.

23:37.640 --> 23:41.268
Yeah, it's free speech,
so there's not much we can do.

23:41.268 --> 23:44.146
Donovan call you back? Nope.

23:44.146 --> 23:45.356
Look, I know
you don't want to put Lila

23:45.356 --> 23:46.816
through any more of this
custody stuff,

23:46.816 --> 23:48.567
but you're not the one
who's doing this.

23:48.567 --> 23:51.070
You know that, right? He is.

23:51.070 --> 23:57.576
He's the one who decided
to move. Yeah. But?

23:57.576 --> 24:00.413
I‐I mean, who am I
to say that he can't?

24:00.413 --> 24:02.915
E‐Especially after
everything that I did.

24:02.915 --> 24:04.250
[ Brakes squeak ]

24:04.250 --> 24:06.877
Okay, you know what?
Maybe I'm wrong,

24:06.877 --> 24:09.422
and maybe I'm bringing
my own experience into this,

24:09.422 --> 24:12.341
but I still think
you're punishing yourself.

24:12.341 --> 24:14.468
Yeah, like, y‐y‐you got this
narrative going right now

24:14.468 --> 24:17.638
where he's the saint
and you're some screw‐up.

24:17.638 --> 24:19.015
And you know what?
I‐I don't know.

24:19.015 --> 24:21.434
I wasn't there,
a‐and maybe you were terrible.

24:21.434 --> 24:24.228
But right now,
he's trying to take your kid,

24:24.228 --> 24:25.604
and you're just
letting him do it

24:25.604 --> 24:31.027
because you're so eaten up
with guilt. Like...

24:31.027 --> 24:32.319
[ Exhales slowly ]

24:32.319 --> 24:35.031
Cooper Sanford?
I'm Detective Lopez.

24:35.031 --> 24:36.323
This is Officer Nolan.

24:36.323 --> 24:37.575
Nolan: We're looking
for a friend of yours ‐‐

24:37.575 --> 24:40.202
Marvin Reynolds.
Doesn't ring a bell.

24:40.202 --> 24:41.495
See, now,
that's a dumb thing to say,

24:41.495 --> 24:43.205
because clearly, it does.

24:43.205 --> 24:45.082
We heard that you sold him
thousands of dollars' worth

24:45.082 --> 24:46.459
of Sovereign Citizen kits.

24:46.459 --> 24:48.085
[ Chuckles ]

24:48.085 --> 24:50.588
And who told you that?
We're not
telling you that.

24:50.588 --> 24:52.298
Yeah, probably
his bitch of a girlfriend.

24:52.298 --> 24:53.632
He dumped her and moved on.

24:53.632 --> 24:55.634
Can't believe anything
that she says.

24:55.634 --> 24:57.928
So you <i>do</i> know him.

24:57.928 --> 25:00.264
I'm gonna need to see
your delegation of authority.

25:00.264 --> 25:01.599
It's right here.

25:01.599 --> 25:03.434
When was the last time you were
in contact with Marvin?

25:03.434 --> 25:05.770
I don't need to answer
any of your questions.

25:05.770 --> 25:07.772
I'm not a citizen
of your corporation.

25:07.772 --> 25:10.191
My corporation? In 1871,

25:10.191 --> 25:12.276
the United States
stopped being a country

25:12.276 --> 25:13.944
and started being a corporation.

25:13.944 --> 25:16.072
None of the laws passed
since then in any ‐‐

25:16.072 --> 25:18.616
Enough of the
Sovereign Citizen crap!

25:18.616 --> 25:20.826
You need to educate yourself!

25:20.826 --> 25:24.455
This "government" that you serve
sells us all into slavery!

25:24.455 --> 25:26.665
Marvin is planning
a terrorist act.

25:26.665 --> 25:28.584
Do you understand that?

25:28.584 --> 25:29.919
If you have
any knowledge of it,

25:29.919 --> 25:31.378
you're an accessory
after the fact,

25:31.378 --> 25:36.217
whether you believe in the law
or not. I'm not scared of you!

25:36.217 --> 25:40.096
[ Flat Worms'
"Surreal New Year" plays ]

25:40.096 --> 25:41.514
Nolan: Whoa, whoa, whoa.

25:41.514 --> 25:42.598
♪♪

25:42.598 --> 25:44.100
I'm gonna cut him off.

25:44.100 --> 25:45.643
♪ Establishing bricks ♪

25:45.643 --> 25:50.439
Clear it out. Go.
Move out.

25:50.439 --> 25:52.483
♪ ...in your hands ♪

25:52.483 --> 25:54.860
[ Wood chipper motor whirring ]

25:54.860 --> 25:55.986
Get out!

25:55.986 --> 25:57.655
♪♪

25:57.655 --> 25:59.323
[ Music stops ]

26:01.033 --> 26:03.160
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

26:03.160 --> 26:05.371
Cooper:
[ Groans ]

26:05.371 --> 26:08.374
[ Grunting ]

26:08.374 --> 26:09.625
Let's try this again.

26:09.625 --> 26:12.044
Where's your friend?
What's he got planned?

26:12.044 --> 26:14.755
I do not recognize
your authority.

26:14.755 --> 26:16.382
I do not answer questions.

26:16.382 --> 26:18.509
You will tell me,
or a lot of people will die.

26:18.509 --> 26:20.302
I do not recognize
your authority!

26:20.302 --> 26:24.265
I do not answer questions!
I could change that.

26:24.265 --> 26:26.600
Aah!
Come on! What are you doing?

26:26.600 --> 26:27.935
I need a lawyer!

26:27.935 --> 26:29.520
See, all these guys
embrace the legal system

26:29.520 --> 26:30.521
when it serves them!

26:30.521 --> 26:32.857
You need to stop now,
Angela. Out of my way!

26:32.857 --> 26:40.698
Take a step back. I outrank you.
Take a step back, ma'am. Aah.

26:40.698 --> 26:42.867
[ Exhales sharply ]

26:42.867 --> 26:44.660
She was trying to hurt me.

26:44.660 --> 26:47.204
No. She was trying to
scare you.

26:47.204 --> 26:49.415
Now, I could charge you
right now with assault ‐‐

26:49.415 --> 26:52.459
Yeah, and I could file
a complaint for abuse.

26:52.459 --> 26:54.211
That is a stretch.

26:54.211 --> 26:55.796
Look, I am willing to
uncuff you right now.

26:55.796 --> 26:58.048
We can put this whole thing
in both our rearview mirrors,

26:58.048 --> 27:01.594
but only if you tell me
what Marvin was planning.

27:01.594 --> 27:03.596
Now, believe this ‐‐

27:03.596 --> 27:06.891
the detective
was telling the truth.

27:06.891 --> 27:08.893
If Marvin hurts someone
and you're withholding evidence,

27:08.893 --> 27:10.394
you will be charged
right alongside of him.

27:10.394 --> 27:12.229
And good luck
telling the prison guards

27:12.229 --> 27:13.981
you don't believe in
their authority.

27:13.981 --> 27:17.026
[ Siren wailing ]

27:17.026 --> 27:20.196
I don't know
where Marvin is.

27:20.196 --> 27:22.448
He called me
about an hour ago.

27:22.448 --> 27:27.620
He asked me to meet him,
bring my guns.

27:27.620 --> 27:30.998
I told him I was all talk
and that he was on his own.

27:30.998 --> 27:33.751
What did he say
he needed the guns for?

27:33.751 --> 27:36.795
He just said
it was go time.

27:36.795 --> 27:39.924
And that I'd probably
never see him again.

27:39.924 --> 27:41.050
♪♪

27:44.637 --> 27:45.804
[ Engine revs ]

27:45.804 --> 27:46.847
Maybe I should
just let it go,

27:46.847 --> 27:48.682
but that house
was my childhood home.

27:48.682 --> 27:50.184
I don't want to
tear it down.

27:50.184 --> 27:51.352
I want another family
to live there

27:51.352 --> 27:54.021
and make happy memories.
Of course.

27:54.021 --> 27:56.440
I moved out 10 years ago,
and when I think of home,

27:56.440 --> 27:58.275
I still think of
my parents' house.

27:58.275 --> 27:59.944
[ Tires screech ]

27:59.944 --> 28:06.075
What's wrong? Tim?

28:06.075 --> 28:08.619
Look, I know you don't feel
the same way I do,

28:08.619 --> 28:14.166
but our childhood
wasn't all bad. Stop. Alright?

28:14.166 --> 28:16.835
Are you really getting nostalgic
over that place?

28:16.835 --> 28:18.837
What ‐‐ What do you want?
Some other family

28:18.837 --> 28:20.714
to just cuddle up
under the broken plaster

28:20.714 --> 28:23.425
where dad slammed my head
against the wall?

28:23.425 --> 28:28.347
Dad had a lot of demons.
Dad was a monster. He's changed.

28:28.347 --> 28:30.307
You haven't seen him
in 20 years.

28:30.307 --> 28:32.142
The only thing
that's changed

28:32.142 --> 28:33.644
is that the drinking
caught up with him.

28:33.644 --> 28:34.895
Okay?
He can't throw a punch,

28:34.895 --> 28:36.647
but he's the same guy
underneath.

28:36.647 --> 28:39.900
He's not, and you'd know that
if you'd visit the hospice.

28:39.900 --> 28:43.153
Not in a million years.
Wait, hospice?

28:43.153 --> 28:47.658
I had to move him out of
assisted living last month.

28:47.658 --> 28:49.201
Dad's dying.

28:49.201 --> 28:58.252
♪♪

28:58.252 --> 29:01.296
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

29:01.296 --> 29:06.510
I know you and Wesley

29:06.510 --> 29:09.179
are going through a lot
right now, but that's no excuse.

29:09.179 --> 29:10.639
I wasn't actually
going to hurt him.

29:10.639 --> 29:12.391
It doesn't matter.

29:12.391 --> 29:14.184
We can't play "bad cop"
anymore.

29:14.184 --> 29:15.894
We have to rise above
that way of thinking

29:15.894 --> 29:19.189
because it's corrosive.

29:19.189 --> 29:23.235
You're right.
I'm sorry. Thank you.

29:23.235 --> 29:25.612
Silver Honda ‐‐
that could be Marvin's car.

29:25.612 --> 29:27.573
Plate's a match.
That's him.

29:27.573 --> 29:30.367
Control, 7‐Adam‐15, we have eyes
on Marvin Reynolds' vehicle.

29:30.367 --> 29:31.702
Stand by.

29:31.702 --> 29:34.747
[ Bass thumping in distance ]

29:40.210 --> 29:41.754
[ Sighs ]

29:41.754 --> 29:43.547
7‐Adam‐100, 7‐Adam‐15,

29:43.547 --> 29:45.340
we've cleared the vehicle,
no sign of suspect.

29:45.340 --> 29:46.717
Tim: <i>Secure the location</i>
<i>and sit tight</i>

29:46.717 --> 29:51.847
<i>until TID arrives.</i>
Copy that. Lopez, you see this?

29:51.847 --> 29:53.265
Oil leak.

29:53.265 --> 29:55.517
There was a big vehicle here
parked for some time.

29:55.517 --> 29:57.686
The street cleaners had to
maneuver around it.

29:57.686 --> 29:59.063
Another weapons stash?

29:59.063 --> 30:01.273
So he ditched the Civic
and drove off in an arsenal?

30:01.273 --> 30:02.483
Woman:
You finally got rid of it.

30:02.483 --> 30:04.693
Rid of what? That van.

30:04.693 --> 30:06.779
I must've called a hundred times
trying to get it towed.

30:06.779 --> 30:10.032
Well, then, uh, you must
remember some details about it?

30:10.032 --> 30:13.744
Yeah.

30:13.744 --> 30:16.288
Hey, I‐I know a great
bereavement counselor,

30:16.288 --> 30:17.956
if you need someone
to talk to.

30:17.956 --> 30:20.793
I have someone. Thanks.

30:20.793 --> 30:22.169
You know, therapy's really
helped me come to terms

30:22.169 --> 30:26.173
with everything that happened
to us when we were kids.

30:26.173 --> 30:29.718
It could help you, too. I'm good.

30:29.718 --> 30:31.845
You really don't think
you carry some trauma

30:31.845 --> 30:33.430
from what
he put you through?

30:33.430 --> 30:34.640
When you were 7 years old,

30:34.640 --> 30:36.100
he dropped you in Griffith Park
with a compass

30:36.100 --> 30:38.560
and made you
find your way home. Which I did.

30:38.560 --> 30:42.606
A Tim Test. A what?
Nothing. Um...

30:42.606 --> 30:43.857
[ Computer beeps ]

30:43.857 --> 30:47.277
Oh. We got a hit on the van
that Nolan and Lopez I. D.'d.

30:47.277 --> 30:49.655
It's racked up
hundreds of dollars in fines.

30:49.655 --> 30:52.950
Parking tickets? And tolls.
Where are they clustered?

30:52.950 --> 30:54.535
Uh, they're centered around
the Port of Los Angeles.

30:54.535 --> 30:55.786
Didn't the intel report
state

30:55.786 --> 30:56.870
that Marvin used to work
down there?

30:56.870 --> 30:58.205
Drove a forklift
or something?

30:58.205 --> 30:59.498
Yeah, but he was fired
two years ago.

30:59.498 --> 31:01.959
Why would he
be visiting now?

31:01.959 --> 31:03.335
I'll send some units.

31:03.335 --> 31:05.754
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

31:05.754 --> 31:07.840
Air Three has eyes
on suspect vehicle.

31:07.840 --> 31:10.008
Northeast corner of lot A,
just off Front Street.

31:10.008 --> 31:11.135
I'm gonna orbit.

31:11.135 --> 31:14.179
Control, 7‐Adam‐15,
show us responding.

31:14.179 --> 31:16.014
[ Engine revs ]

31:16.014 --> 31:20.644
Harper: Air Three, 7‐Adam‐07,
arriving at location. Stand by.

31:20.644 --> 31:25.357
♪♪

31:25.357 --> 31:28.652
Air Three, 7‐Adam‐07,
any movement?

31:28.652 --> 31:30.237
♪♪

31:30.237 --> 31:33.365
7‐Adam‐07, I see no movement
in suspect vehicle.

31:33.365 --> 31:38.203
♪♪

31:38.203 --> 31:41.540
Aaron, relax
and follow my lead.

31:41.540 --> 31:48.213
♪♪

31:48.213 --> 31:54.887
♪♪

31:54.887 --> 31:56.096
Front seat clear.

31:56.096 --> 32:02.811
♪♪

32:02.811 --> 32:09.526
♪♪

32:09.526 --> 32:13.030
Clear.

32:13.030 --> 32:15.782
Air Three, 7‐Adam‐07,
no sign of suspect,

32:15.782 --> 32:17.910
but he is
clearly well‐armed.

32:17.910 --> 32:21.246
Marvin just posted something
to social media.

32:21.246 --> 32:24.917
<i>History is gonna remember</i>
<i>this day as Sovereigns' Day.</i>

32:24.917 --> 32:26.376
<i>I'm about to light the spark</i>

32:26.376 --> 32:28.170
<i>that's gonna ignite</i>
<i>the revolution.</i>

32:28.170 --> 32:30.547
Maybe we can spot something
that gives away his location.

32:30.547 --> 32:31.798
It's hard to tell.

32:31.798 --> 32:35.469
And who knows
when he recorded that.

32:35.469 --> 32:36.553
Aaron:
I mean, why here?

32:36.553 --> 32:38.680
Uh, there are dozens of targets
at the port,

32:38.680 --> 32:41.099
from the cruise ship terminal
to the port itself.

32:41.099 --> 32:43.268
Yeah, or maybe he's here to kill
the boss that fired him

32:43.268 --> 32:45.103
and pretend
it's for some great cause.

32:45.103 --> 32:46.104
[ Gunshots ]

32:46.104 --> 32:47.689
[ Glass shatters ]

32:47.689 --> 32:49.274
We're taking fire!
We need to back off!

32:49.274 --> 32:51.360
Do you have a location
on the shooter?

32:51.360 --> 32:55.658
Negative, negative.
Where the hell is he?

32:58.213 --> 32:59.589
[ Gunfire ]

32:59.589 --> 33:00.799
Harper: Air Three,
suspect heading north

33:00.799 --> 33:02.676
along the water,
armed with a long gun.

33:02.676 --> 33:04.553
Pilot: <i>We're climbing to a safe</i>
<i>altitude, then I'll swing back.</i>

33:04.553 --> 33:06.388
Police, stop!

33:13.103 --> 33:14.229
[ Grunts ]

33:14.229 --> 33:20.068
Control, 7‐Adam‐07,
alert Long Beach Police,

33:20.068 --> 33:21.737
we are taking fire.

33:21.737 --> 33:25.490
Moving to channel 13
for mutual aid.

33:25.490 --> 33:26.742
Secure that weapon.

33:26.742 --> 33:30.036
♪♪

33:30.036 --> 33:37.711
Aaron: [ Panting ]

33:37.711 --> 33:39.588
We have to stop him before
he gets on that ship.

33:39.588 --> 33:43.717
♪♪

33:43.717 --> 33:46.011
[ People screaming ]

33:46.011 --> 33:48.847
[ Gunshots ]

33:48.847 --> 33:54.227
♪♪

33:54.227 --> 33:57.230
[ Sirens wailing ]

33:57.230 --> 34:02.486
♪♪

34:02.486 --> 34:05.030
Clear!

34:05.030 --> 34:09.451
Move! Clear!
Everyone, clear! What do you got?

34:09.451 --> 34:10.911
Single shooter we've been
tracking since L. A.

34:10.911 --> 34:14.748
Where is he?
Somewhere on that boat.

34:14.748 --> 34:17.459
Stay here
in case he doubles back.

34:17.459 --> 34:19.211
Nolan: Move, move, move!
Come, come.

34:19.211 --> 34:21.546
♪♪

34:21.546 --> 34:22.964
We should split up.

34:22.964 --> 34:32.182
♪♪

34:32.182 --> 34:33.975
Covering.

34:33.975 --> 34:35.060
♪♪

34:35.060 --> 34:36.728
Clear. Clear.

34:36.728 --> 34:38.355
♪♪

34:38.355 --> 34:39.731
Clear.

34:39.731 --> 34:42.025
♪♪

34:42.025 --> 34:43.193
Clear.

34:43.193 --> 34:45.779
♪♪

34:45.779 --> 34:46.947
Lopez: Holding.

34:46.947 --> 34:48.323
♪♪

34:48.323 --> 34:49.825
Nolan: Clear.

34:49.825 --> 34:53.203
♪♪

34:53.203 --> 34:54.412
Holding.

34:54.412 --> 34:55.831
♪♪

34:55.831 --> 34:56.957
[ Door knob rattles ]
Go.

34:56.957 --> 34:58.416
♪♪

34:58.416 --> 35:01.002
Oh.
It's okay. Stay calm.

35:01.002 --> 35:02.254
Keep going going this way,
exit the ship.

35:02.254 --> 35:04.089
There's other officers
waiting outside.

35:04.089 --> 35:12.139
♪♪

35:12.139 --> 35:13.557
Harper:
Exit out that door.

35:13.557 --> 35:15.308
It's a straight shot outside,
okay?

35:15.308 --> 35:18.478
It's clear.
We just came from that way. Go.

35:18.478 --> 35:24.276
♪♪

35:24.276 --> 35:25.652
Aaron:
It's all clear.

35:25.652 --> 35:30.365
♪♪

35:30.365 --> 35:32.200
Clear.

35:32.200 --> 35:33.493
♪♪

35:33.493 --> 35:34.327
Clear.

35:34.327 --> 35:35.370
[ Rattling ]

35:35.370 --> 35:36.413
[ Whispering ] Lopez.

35:44.713 --> 35:46.423
Don't move!
It's okay.

35:46.423 --> 35:47.507
Whoa.
You're safe, you're safe.

35:47.507 --> 35:48.633
Please.
Please get me out of here.

35:48.633 --> 35:49.593
Please get me out of here.

35:49.593 --> 35:51.094
You have to let him go
first.

35:51.094 --> 35:52.387
Okay.
I‐I'm sorry.
That's alright.

35:52.387 --> 35:53.471
[ Clank ]
[ Gasps ]

35:53.471 --> 35:55.015
What is that?

35:55.015 --> 35:56.266
You stay here.
You'll be safe, alright?

35:56.266 --> 35:57.434
Please don't leave me!

35:57.434 --> 35:59.102
Just lock the door
behind us.

35:59.102 --> 36:02.397
♪♪

36:02.397 --> 36:04.191
[ Lock clicks ]

36:04.191 --> 36:05.609
Hey!

36:05.609 --> 36:07.527
[ Gunshots ]

36:07.527 --> 36:08.778
♪♪

36:08.778 --> 36:11.781
[ Gunfire ]

36:11.781 --> 36:21.750
♪♪

36:21.750 --> 36:23.210
Lopez:
[ Grunts ]

36:23.210 --> 36:30.091
♪♪

36:30.091 --> 36:35.722
♪♪

36:35.722 --> 36:41.394
♪♪

36:41.394 --> 36:44.397
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

36:44.397 --> 36:52.489
♪♪

36:52.489 --> 37:00.622
♪♪

37:00.622 --> 37:08.797
♪♪

37:08.797 --> 37:16.972
♪♪

37:16.972 --> 37:19.140
Drop it!

37:19.140 --> 37:20.183
[ Gunshots ]

37:20.183 --> 37:26.064
♪♪

37:26.064 --> 37:28.400
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

37:28.400 --> 37:33.145
♪♪

37:38.477 --> 37:39.457
You're right.
About what?

37:39.457 --> 37:41.167
I need to fight for Lila.

37:41.167 --> 37:43.615
Even if I lose,
she needs to know

37:43.615 --> 37:46.118
that I would do anything
for her. You're not gonna lose.

37:46.118 --> 37:47.619
[ Sighs ]

37:48.704 --> 37:49.621
[ Cameras beep ]

37:49.621 --> 37:51.373
Yeah, I'm not so sure.

37:51.373 --> 37:55.335
I mean, my lawyer is
a lovely person but...

37:55.335 --> 37:57.629
Actually, that might be
the issue.

37:57.629 --> 38:00.007
She's too nice
to be a divorce lawyer.

38:00.007 --> 38:02.509
Well, then hire
someone better ‐‐ or worse.

38:02.509 --> 38:04.136
Better lawyer,
worse person.

38:04.136 --> 38:07.181
Me and whose paycheck?
Use my lawyer.

38:07.181 --> 38:11.059
She is a shark,
and she owes me one.

38:11.059 --> 38:13.479
The press around my trial
tripled her business.

38:13.479 --> 38:15.314
She'll give you
the friends and family discount.

38:15.314 --> 38:17.399
I'll send you the details.

38:17.399 --> 38:19.026
Thanks.
Happy to help.

38:19.026 --> 38:20.986
[ Chance Peña's "Anxiety
& Mixed Emotions" plays ]

38:20.986 --> 38:22.988
Hey.
Lucy: Hm? Where's Genny?

38:22.988 --> 38:25.449
Oh, she is
calling your nephews.

38:25.449 --> 38:31.747
Um, Tim, listen, uh...
Your sister needs you.

38:31.747 --> 38:35.000
Lucy...
I‐I realize
that I'm overstepping here,

38:35.000 --> 38:37.211
but just hear me out.

38:37.211 --> 38:38.670
It's clear that
you got the worst of it

38:38.670 --> 38:39.630
with your father,

38:39.630 --> 38:41.632
but she lived through it
with you.

38:41.632 --> 38:45.260
Instead of arguing about
how bad your dad was or wasn't,

38:45.260 --> 38:50.265
maybe as ‐‐ as children
of abuse,

38:50.265 --> 38:53.018
you would be better off
just supporting each other.

38:53.018 --> 38:57.272
Hey.
You ready to go? Yeah.

38:57.272 --> 39:00.317
Look, I'm really sorry
about today.

39:00.317 --> 39:03.612
I should've listened more.
I agree.

39:03.612 --> 39:04.822
♪ Tell me that I'm worth it ♪

39:04.822 --> 39:08.033
But thanks for saying it.
That means a lot.

39:08.033 --> 39:09.952
I'm still not going to
see him.

39:09.952 --> 39:12.204
♪ ...I think about ♪

39:12.204 --> 39:15.123
Oh, uh, Nolan,
this is my sister Genny.

39:15.123 --> 39:16.875
Oh! Nice to finally meet you
in person.

39:16.875 --> 39:19.127
I'm so grateful you're willing
to help out with dad's house.

39:19.127 --> 39:20.420
Ah, it's my pleasure.

39:20.420 --> 39:21.880
You know, if you're free
this weekend,

39:21.880 --> 39:23.757
maybe we could go by the place,
see what needs to be done,

39:23.757 --> 39:25.092
and you could give us
an estimate.

39:25.092 --> 39:28.428
Did you just say "we"?
As in you're gonna help?

39:28.428 --> 39:31.181
Well, I checked out some comps
in the neighborhood,

39:31.181 --> 39:33.976
and we can get a million
for that place, easy.

39:33.976 --> 39:38.730
Plus, it shouldn't all
fall on you. Thanks.

39:38.730 --> 39:42.860
I'll see you both
Saturday. Nolan.

39:42.860 --> 39:45.279
One second.
Come here.

39:45.279 --> 39:48.866
Hey, can I have
everyone's attention, please?

39:48.866 --> 39:51.076
♪ ...what this world
has for me ♪

39:51.076 --> 39:53.161
